================================================================================
RAM Tester - Lizenzen / Licenses
================================================================================

Project:  RAM Tester for vintage DRAM / SRAM (ATmega328P)
Author:   Andreas Hoffmann
Source:   https://github.com/tops4u/Ram-Tester/

This project is split into two licensing domains:

  * FIRMWARE / SOFTWARE (the application code, all .cpp/.h/.ino sources)
        -> GNU General Public License v3.0 or later   (SPDX: GPL-3.0-or-later)

  * HARDWARE (schematics, PCB layout, Gerber files, KiCad project, BOM)
        -> CERN Open Hardware Licence v2 - Strongly Reciprocal
                                                      (SPDX: CERN-OHL-S-2.0)

Software and hardware are licensed SEPARATELY and on purpose: the GPL is a
software copyright licence and maps poorly onto a physical board, whereas the
CERN-OHL-S is purpose-built for open hardware (it defines "Source", "Product"
and the obligations that arise when someone manufactures a product from the
design). Both are strongly reciprocal (copyleft), so the open spirit is the
same across the whole project.

The two canonical, unmodified licence texts ship alongside this file:
        gpl-3.0.txt            (full GNU GPL v3 text)
        cern_ohl_s_v2.txt      (full CERN-OHL-S v2 text)
In any conflict, those canonical texts are authoritative over the summaries
below.

This file also lists the third-party components, routines and fonts that the
FIRMWARE incorporates, with their respective licenses.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Overview of components and their licenses
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1. RAM Tester firmware / application code .... GNU GPL v3.0-or-later
  2. RAM Tester hardware design files .......... CERN-OHL-S v2
  3. avr-libc (AVR / ATmega routines) .......... 3-clause (modified) BSD
     Arduino Core (Arduino.h) .................. GNU LGPL 2.1-or-later
  4. U8g2 graphics library (HEAVILY MODIFIED) .. new-BSD (2-clause BSD)
  5. Fonts:
       - u8g2_font_7x14B_tr      (M_Font) ...... Public Domain (X11 misc-fixed)
       - u8g2_font_version_custom (S_Font) ..... Public Domain (X11 misc-fixed)
       - open_iconic_check_4x    (icons) ....... SIL Open Font License 1.1
       - open_iconic_embedded_4x (icons) ....... SIL Open Font License 1.1

NOTE on fonts: The Adobe X11 font-license section (COUR / HELV / NCEN / TIM /
SYMB) that ships inside the U8g2 LICENSE file is reproduced in the APPENDIX at
the very end for completeness ONLY. None of those Adobe-derived fonts are used
by this project - the fonts actually used are the four listed above.


