MERCHANTABILITY, SATISFACTORY QUALITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.
Please see the CERN-OHL-S v2 for applicable conditions.

Source location: https://github.com/tops4u/Ram-Tester/

As per CERN-OHL-S v2 section 4, should You produce hardware based on this
source, You must where practicable maintain the Source Location visible on the
external case of the Gizmo (e.g. the tester PCB) or other products you make
using this source.

The complete text of the CERN-OHL-S v2 ships as "cern_ohl_s_v2.txt" next to this
file and is also available at:
    https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt

SPDX-License-Identifier: CERN-OHL-S-2.0

Recommended notice to keep inside the design files (e.g. KiCad text layer / a
LICENSE note travelling with the Gerbers): the five lines above beginning
"This source describes Open Hardware ...".


================================================================================
3) avr-libc (AVR / ATmega routines) and Arduino Core
================================================================================

This project uses avr-libc - the AVR / ATmega run-time routines and the
register / peripheral definitions for the ATmega328P (e.g. <avr/io.h>,
<avr/pgmspace.h>, <util/delay.h>, <avr/interrupt.h>).

avr-libc is distributed under a 3-clause (modified) BSD license by its
respective copyright holders. License and details:
    https://www.nongnu.org/avr-libc/    (see the avr-libc "LICENSE" file)

The project also uses components of the Arduino platform (Arduino.h), which are
licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL), Version 2.1 or
later:
    https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.1.html


================================================================================
4) U8g2 graphics library
================================================================================

IMPORTANT: This project does NOT ship the unmodified upstream U8g2 library. It
contains a HEAVILY MODIFIED / stripped-down variant of U8g2 - reduced to the few
parts needed for this tester and adapted with project-specific patches (e.g. an
I2C 400 kHz timing fix). The original U8g2 new-BSD license below continues to
apply to all U8g2-derived portions.

------------ new-BSD License for U8g2lib Code ------------

